Successive Over-Relaxation

Here, we explore the effect of the weighting in the Successive Over-Relaxation scheme.

Optimal Correction

$\omega = \frac{2}{1+\sqrt{1-\lambda}}$ with $\lambda = \frac{1}{4}\left(\cos{\pi / n_i}+\cos{\pi / n_j}\right)^2$

(In this case, $\omega = 1.85$)

Under-corrected

$0<\omega<1$

(In this case, $\omega = 0.5$)

Over-Corrected

$1\le\omega<2$

(In this case, $\omega = 1.99$)
